race.comment: MAXILDO (4) is back in grade and might be ready to take the race by the scruff of the neck. He has more ability than most in this field and will likely roll forward with the claim. He won his only start and this track and will enjoy the sting out of the ground. Expect he will be hard to beat. BLUE SPECIAL (3) is racing well this campaign and can win again. He mixes his form but he'll get a cosy run from barrier one under Murtagh. He can be finishing hard. Expecting to see some improvement from AGREEANCE (9), who is having her second run for the new stable. She is much better suited at 1600m. Others to consider here include the local ALLEGEDLY (2) and the old warrior FRANCE'S BOY (1).
